Hey Cllaude271,
To have gone through the state you describe (after a mix of gossips, micropoints, taz, keta, in short everything that passed through there),
If I can give you advice, it's just to tell you that it's all just psychological.
The more you stress about it, the worse it'll get.
A pretty simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe softly, and you lean into a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you might feel like they're closing in on you).
After several months of use, especially when mixing, you can still find effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Cllaude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that clutter your head.
Keep the fish, and stay positive.
